<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6781697-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7103"><num value="7103">§ 7103.</num><heading> Licenses for radio officers</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6781698-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7103/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> A license as radio officer may be issued only to an applicant who has a first-class or second-class radiotelegraph operator license issued by the Federal Communications Commission.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6781699-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7103/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> Except as provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s7318">section 7318 of this title</ref>, this part does not affect the status of radiotelegraph operators serving on board vessels operating only on the Great Lakes.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf678169a-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/540">97 Stat. 540</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf678169b-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
